  <oversight_info>
    <authority>Denmark: The Regional Committee on Biomedical Research Ethics</authority>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of the present study is to compare two novel molecular based diagnostic
      tests for Bacterial Vaginosis, a PNA FISH and a PCR method with conventional Gram staining
      for abnormal vaginal flora detection in a Danish IVF-setting. We hope to introduce a new
      clinical practice in testing and diagnosing Bacterial Vaginosis.

      We hypothesize that the molecular based tests will prove more efficient than conventional
      Gram staining.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
